---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Kenyan Chilli | Victoria Herbs & Spices – Africa's Boldest Heat"
  description="Kenyan Bird's Eye Chilli: Grown in Africa's Great Rift Valley. 80,000-100,000 SHU of pure, sun-dried heat. Hand-harvested by smallholder farmers. Traceable, potent, exceptional."
>
  <!-- Hero Section - The Heat of Africa -->
  <section
    class="relative h-screen flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden"
  >
    <!-- Background with dramatic chilli image -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/chilli.jpg"
        alt="Vibrant red Kenyan chillies"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-stone-900/95 via-stone-900/80 to-stone-900/40"
      >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center">
      <!-- Heat Scale Badge -->
      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-orange-500/20 backdrop-blur-lg px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-orange-300 text-sm mb-8 border border-orange-500/30"
      >
        <span class="relative flex h-3 w-3">
          <span
            class="animate-ping absolute inline-flex h-full w-full rounded-full bg-orange-400 opacity-75"
          ></span>
          <span class="relative inline-flex rounded-full h-3 w-3 bg-orange-500"
          ></span>
        </span>
        <span class="font-mono">80,000 - 100,000 SHU</span>
        <span class="text-white/50 mx-2">•</span>
        <span>🔥 Africa's Hottest</span>
      </div>

      <h1
        class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-display font-bold text-white leading-tight"
      >
        Forged by<br />
        <span
          class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-400 to-red-500"
        >
          African Sun
        </span>
      </h1>

      <p
        class="mt-6 text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
      >
        Grown in Kenya's Great Rift Valley — where intense equatorial sun,
        volcanic soils, and generations of farming knowledge combine to create
        chillies of exceptional heat, color, and complexity.
      </p>

      <!-- Heat Visualization -->
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-12">
        <div class="flex justify-between text-xs text-white/50 mb-2">
          <span>Jalapeño</span>
          <span>Cayenne</span>
          <span>Thai</span>
          <span class="text-orange-400 font-bold">Kenyan Bird's Eye</span>
          <span>Habanero</span>
        </div>
        <div
          class="h-3 bg-stone-800/50 rounded-full overflow-hidden backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div
            class="h-full w-3/4 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-400 via-red-500 to-red-600 relative"
            style="width: 85%"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-white animate-pulse"
            >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5 justify-center mt-16">
        <a
          href="#heat-origin"
          class="group px-8 py-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-red-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:from-orange-600 hover:to-red-700 transition-all shadow-lg shadow-orange-600/20 inline-flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          Discover the Heat
          <svg
            class="w-5 h-5 group-hover:translate-y-1 transition-transform"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M19 14l-7 7-7-7m14-6l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/contact?quote=true&product=chilli"
          class="px-8 py-4 border-2 border-white/30 text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-white/10 hover:border-white/50 transition backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          Request Sample
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scroll Indicator -->
    <div
      class="absolute bottom-8 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 flex flex-col items-center text-white/40 text-xs tracking-widest"
    >
      <span>SCROLL TO FEEL THE HEAT</span>
      <div
        class="w-px h-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-white/30 to-transparent mt-2"
      >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Heat Origin Story -->
  <section id="heat-origin" class="py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span
            class="text-orange-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
            >The Science of Heat</span
          >
          <h2
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900 leading-tight"
          >
            Why Kenyan Chillies<br />Burn Brighter
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 mt-8 text-stone-700">
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              The Scoville Scale measures capsaicin concentration — the compound
              that creates heat. Kenyan Bird's Eye Chillies consistently test at <span
                class="font-bold text-orange-600">80,000-100,000 SHU</span
              >, placing them among the hottest naturally-grown chillies in the
              world.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              But heat isn't just about numbers. It's about <span
                class="font-semibold">complexity</span
              > — the way the initial burn evolves into fruity, smoky notes. Our
              chillies develop this complexity through stress: intense sun, high
              altitude, and mineral-rich volcanic soils force the plants to produce
              more capsaicin as a natural defense.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Scoville Comparison -->
          <div
            class="mt-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-50 to-red-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-orange-200"
          >
            <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-4">
              Scoville Heat Units Comparison
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Bell Pepper</span>
                  <span>0 SHU</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div class="h-full w-0 bg-stone-400 rounded-full"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Jalapeño</span>
                  <span>2,500 - 8,000 SHU</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[5%] bg-green-500 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 5%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Cayenne</span>
                  <span>30,000 - 50,000 SHU</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[30%] bg-yellow-500 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 35%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span class="font-bold text-orange-600"
                    >Kenyan Bird's Eye</span
                  >
                  <span class="font-bold text-orange-600"
                    >80,000 - 100,000 SHU</span
                  >
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-[85%] bg-orange-500 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 85%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-1">
                  <span>Habanero</span>
                  <span>100,000 - 350,000 SHU</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-stone-200 rounded-full">
                  <div
                    class="h-full w-full bg-red-500 rounded-full"
                    style="width: 100%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-4">
              *Our chillies are naturally grown, selectively bred for heat, not
              genetically modified
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Terroir Cards -->
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-orange-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">☀️</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Intense Equatorial Sun
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  Positioned at the equator, our chilli farms receive 12+ hours
                  of direct sunlight daily. This UV intensity triggers stress
                  responses in the plants, increasing capsaicin production as a
                  natural defense mechanism. More sun = more heat.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-orange-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">🌋</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Volcanic Rift Valley Soils
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  The Great Rift Valley's volcanic soils are rich in potassium
                  and phosphorus — essential nutrients for capsaicin synthesis.
                  Combined with well-draining slopes, this creates the perfect
                  terroir for intensely flavored chillies.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-orange-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">⛰️</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  High-Altitude Stress
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  Grown at 1,200-1,800 meters, our chillies experience cool
                  nights that slow ripening, allowing complex flavor compounds
                  to develop. This temperature swing between day and night is
                  crucial for building layered heat profiles.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-stone-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-orange-200 transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
              <div class="text-5xl">💧</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">
                  Rain-Fed Stress
                </h3>
                <p class="text-stone-600">
                  We never irrigate. Our chillies rely solely on seasonal rains,
                  creating controlled water stress that concentrates flavors and
                  heat. The result? Smaller, more potent chillies with
                  exceptional shelf stability.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Anatomy of Kenyan Heat -->
  <section
    class="py-24 bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-900 to-orange-900 text-white"
  >
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <span
          class="text-orange-300 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
          >Beyond the Burn</span
        >
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4">
          The Anatomy of Our Heat
        </h2>
        <p class="text-white/70 text-lg mt-4">
          Kenyan Bird's Eye Chillies aren't just hot — they're complex. Here's
          what makes them unique.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🔥</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Initial Burn</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Immediate, intense heat that hits the front of the tongue. Clean and
            sharp — no bitterness.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🍊</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Fruity Undertones</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Beneath the heat, notes of citrus and tropical fruit emerge — a
            signature of Rift Valley terroir.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🌫️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Smoky Finish</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Slow sun-drying adds subtle smoky undertones that linger after the
            heat subsides.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/10"
        >
          <div class="text-5xl mb-4">⏱️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Sustained Release</h3>
          <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
            Heat builds gradually and lasts — 2-3 minutes of warming sensation,
            not just a quick flash.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cultivation Story -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span
            class="text-orange-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
            >Generations of Knowledge</span
          >
          <h2
            class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900"
          >
            The Farmers Behind the Fire
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 mt-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-700">
              Our chillies are grown by smallholder farmers in Kenya's Machakos,
              Makueni, and Kitui counties — a region known for its resilient
              people and challenging semi-arid climate. These farmers have
              cultivated chillies for generations, perfecting techniques that
              maximize heat while preserving plant health.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-stone-700">
              <span class="font-bold text-orange-600"
                >Traditional seed selection</span
              > is key. Farmers save seeds from the hottest, most disease-resistant
              plants each season, creating locally-adapted varieties that thrive
              in their specific microclimates.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Farmer Quote -->
          <div
            class="mt-10 bg-amber-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-orange-500"
          >
            <p class="text-stone-700 italic">
              "My father taught me: the hottest chillies come from the toughest
              plants. When the rains are scarce, the heat is intense. You can
              taste the struggle in every bite."
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 font-semibold text-stone-900">— Mutua Nzomo</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">
              Chilli farmer, Makueni County • 4th generation
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <img
            src="/chilli.jpg"
            alt="Fresh Kenyan chillies"
            class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl w-full h-64 object-cover"
          />
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594232202007-3477c8ac1b1c?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
            alt="Drying chillies traditionally"
            class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl w-full h-64 object-cover mt-8"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Drying Process -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <span
          class="text-orange-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase"
          >Traditional Methods</span
        >
        <h2
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold mt-4 text-stone-900"
        >
          Sun-Dried to Perfection
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg mt-4">
          We never use mechanical drying. Our chillies are slowly dried under
          the African sun, a traditional process that preserves essential oils
          and develops complex flavors.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4 text-orange-500">☀️</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">7-10 Days in the Sun</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            Spread on raised mats, turned daily for even drying. The slow
            process allows moisture to escape gradually without case-hardening.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4 text-orange-500">🔄</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Night Coverage</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            Each evening, chillies are covered to protect from dew. This daily
            cycle of sun and rest concentrates flavors naturally.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4 text-orange-500">👐</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Hand-Sorted</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-600">
            After drying, each batch is hand-sorted by our women's cooperative —
            removing any imperfect pods, ensuring export quality.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-orange-600 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6"
        >
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Moisture Content: ≤10%</h4>
            <p class="text-orange-100">
              Perfect for long-term storage without mold or quality loss
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Color Retention: 95%+</h4>
            <p class="text-orange-100">
              Sun-drying preserves the vibrant red color buyers expect
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Shelf Life: 24 months</h4>
            <p class="text-orange-100">When stored in cool, dry conditions</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Product Forms -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-stone-900">
          Choose Your Heat
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg mt-4">
          We offer Kenyan chillies in multiple forms to suit your manufacturing,
          blending, or retail needs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Whole Chillies -->
        <div
          class="group bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-50 to-white rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition border border-stone-200"
        >
          <div class="h-56 overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="/chilli.jpg"
              alt="Whole dried chillies"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-700"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Whole Dried</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
              Premium whole Bird's Eye chillies, stems on/off as requested.
              Perfect for wholesale spice markets and further processing.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">MOQ:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">25kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Packaging:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">Poly-lined sacks</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Heat Level:</span><span
                  class="font-bold text-orange-600">80-100k SHU</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
              href="/contact?product=chilli-whole"
              class="block text-center bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-4 rounded-xl transition"
            >
              Request Quote
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chilli Powder -->
        <div
          class="group bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-50 to-white rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition border border-stone-200"
        >
          <div class="h-56 overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596040033229-a9821ebd058d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
              alt="Chilli powder"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-700"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">
              Ground Powder
            </h3>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
              Fine-ground powder with consistent heat and color. Ideal for spice
              blends, sauces, and industrial applications.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">MOQ:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">25kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Grind Size:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">30-40 mesh</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Heat Level:</span><span
                  class="font-bold text-orange-600">80-100k SHU</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
              href="/contact?product=chilli-powder"
              class="block text-center bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-4 rounded-xl transition"
            >
              Request Quote
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chilli Flakes -->
        <div
          class="group bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-50 to-white rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition border border-stone-200"
        >
          <div class="h-56 overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594232202007-3477c8ac1b1c?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80"
              alt="Chilli flakes"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-700"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">
              Crushed Flakes
            </h3>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">
              Coarsely crushed with visible seeds. Perfect for pizzas, pastas,
              oils, and retail packaging.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">MOQ:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">25kg</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Cut Size:</span><span
                  class="font-medium">2-4mm</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span class="text-stone-500">Heat Level:</span><span
                  class="font-bold text-orange-600">80-100k SHU</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
